description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an experienced Registered Nurse looking for a new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a rewarding role where you can work 1:1 with a patient in their own home? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and committed Children&#39;s Nurse to support our service user with his complex care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user is a young boy who lives with his family in Burnley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He has a degenerative neurological condition which causes severe Dystonia and requires a team of nurses to continuously care for him throughout the night to ensure he is safe and support with his clinical care requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be assisting with following clinical tasks;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Continuous respiratory assessment&lt;br /&gt;* Micky Button (Peg Feeding)&lt;br /&gt;* Feeds and flushes required &lt;br /&gt;* Medication Administration&lt;br /&gt;* Personal care &lt;br /&gt;* Moving and handling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Throughout the night he may require comforting by way of gentle reassurance, songs, stories, and cuddles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can apply your valuable skills and experience and deliver exceptional care and support to our service user.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal applicant will hold a valid NMC PIN, have experience in children&#39;s nursing and be able to evidence hands-on clinical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Current NMC PIN&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Neurology &lt;br /&gt;* Children’s Nursing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Night shifts available (10-hour shifts)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will gain great job satisfaction from seeing the positive effects of your hands-on care and how this makes a positive impact on his day to day life.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
